This paper deals with the security of NFC-based transactions, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The study also involves evaluating the effectiveness of ambient sensors as a proximity detection mechanism, which could be considered a human-computer interaction (cs.HC) or a software engineering (cs.SE) topic. Additionally, the paper involves collecting and analyzing data, which could fall under the categories of information retrieval (cs.IR) or cybersecurity (cs.CY).
